616	Egghead	https://cf.geekdo-images.com/thumb/img/xWAUc0RD570-dzmTtwD6vq7J5yo=/fit-in/200x150/pic51109.jpg	https://cf.geekdo-images.com/original/img/tTS-pIKediZyJMYOXsIbF1N0C_U=/0x0/pic51109.jpg	Egghead is a deduction game where players can see everyone else's cards save for their own.  Each turn players read off a question and answer it according to what they see on everyone's cards.  Eventually this gives players enough information to deduce what is on their own cards and winning a point.  This is a very similar version of an idea that appears in the game Code 777, although the question set is considerably different.\n\nSimilar to:\n\n    Code 777\n    What's That on My Head?\n    Amnesia\n    Guess What I Am!\n    Coyote\n    Am I a Banana?\n\n\n\n\n	45	45	45	1974	3	6	6	Robert Abbott
