2730	Quadwrangle	https://cf.geekdo-images.com/thumb/img/VcI_Z5DTkPIs7YNyE5I68TT_to8=/fit-in/200x150/pic55821.jpg	https://cf.geekdo-images.com/original/img/qJvsFpar4YjTzpn2c2NE7dwICKs=/0x0/pic55821.jpg	Quadwrangle is dice game played with a board with 9 columns.  Each column has a counter that starts in the middle and you attempt to move a counter by rolling certain dice combinations to your scoring area.  (It is a bit like playing 9 games of tug of war simultaneously.)  The winner is the first to get 3 counters in their scoring area.\n\nThe dice are rolled in a manner similar to Yahtzee:  Roll 5 dice.  Keep the ones and reroll the rest.  You may reroll up to three times.\n\nThe nine columns are marked:\n-  Number (from 1-6):  Roll a pair of those numbers move the counter 1 space in the column, triple 2 spaces, etc.\n-  Run:  You are trying to roll a straight (12345 for 2 spaces, or 23456 for 3 spaces)\n-  High/Low:  You are trying to roll a total over 23 or under 12.  There are bonuses for rolling more extreme totals.\n\n1996 Mensa Select\n\nReimplemented as:\n\n    Kniffel Duell / Cosmic Cows\n\n\n\n\n	20	20	20	1983	2	2	2	Maureen Hiron
