ave limited replacements; Russian replacement rates escalate as the game goes on.  The objective is to capture the opposition's key cities (for the Russians, Leningrad, Moscow, Stalingrad) or to destroy the other side's army.  The Russian (implicit in rules) can also win by taking Helsinki, Warsaw, and Bucharest, and holding them for two complete turns, but I have never heard of this being done between normal players.\n\nSeveral extremely bad German strategic plans are in wide use.\n\nAvalon Hill Complexity rating - 2\n\n	120	120	120	1963	2	2	2	Charles S. Roberts
